{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"579f64e5-ec19-481","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are continuing implementation work on a ferment for the kubecast project. The previous agent made significant progress but was aborted before finishing. The ferment ID is `019ea6ea-e768-717f-a8f3-63cd6755637b`, phase ID is `phase-1`.\n\n## Current State\n\nThe previous agent completed steps 1-5 (descriptive errors, VariantType in signals, baseline failure handling, FinalizeInput error propagation) and partially completed steps 6-7 (snapshot fallback). Steps 8-11 (tests) were not started.\n\nThere are currently 2 build errors that need fixing first:\n1. `internal/services/clusteradvisor/workflow/analysis_workflow.go:50:24: undefined: uuid` — missing import for `github.com/google/uuid`\n2. `internal/experiments/experimentutils/mocks.go:452:34: cannot use snapshotService` — the snapshots.Service interface was extended with a new method but the mock doesn't implement it\n\n## Files already modified (git diff --stat):\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/debug/service.go` — added sentinel error for metadata missing\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/handler.go` — descriptive error messages + VariantType in signals\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/production_simulator.go` — snapshot fallback logic\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/types/types.go` — VariantType field added\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/workflow/activities.go` — error propagation in FinalizeAnalysis\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/workflow/analysis_workflow.go` — baseline failure detection\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/workflow/types.go` — Error field + VariantType in signal\n- `services/autoscaler/internal/services/snapshots/service.go` — GetRecentSnapshotLocations method added\n\nAlso there's a stray change in `services/autoscaler/Tiltfile` and `services/autoscaler/internal/services/rebalancing/load_rebalancing_params.go` that should be reverted (not part of this ferment).\n\n## What You Need To Do\n\n1. **Fix build errors first** — read the files with errors, fix the uuid import in analysis_workflow.go, and fix the mock in experimentutils/mocks.go (add the missing method to match the new Service interface)\n2. **Revert stray changes** — revert changes to `Tiltfile` and `load_rebalancing_params.go`\n3. **Verify the build passes** — `cd services/autoscaler && go build ./...`\n4. **Review all changes made so far** — read each modified file, verify the implementation matches the spec. Check that:\n   - handler.go: failVariant uses `fmt.Sprintf(\"simulation failed: %s\", cause.Error())` not just the constant\n   - handler.go: VariantType is set in failVariant, success signal, and signalFromVariant\n   - types/types.go: AnalysisVariantCompletedSignal has VariantType field\n   - workflow/types.go: VariantCompletedSignal has VariantType field, FinalizeInput has Error field\n   - workflow/analysis_workflow.go: captures baselineVariantID from EmitBaselineVariant, detects baseline failure in signal handler\n   - workflow/activities.go: FinalizeAnalysis sets analysis.Error when status is failed\n   - production_simulator.go: snapshot fallback for full_cluster path (SourcePlanID == nil && SnapshotAnchorTime == nil)\n   - snapshots/service.go: GetRecentSnapshotLocations method\n   - debug/service.go: sentinel error for metadata missing\n5. **Complete any incomplete step work** — look at what steps the previous agent started but didn't complete via the ferment tools, and call complete_ferment_step for them\n6. **Start and complete steps 6-7** if not already completed\n7. **Implement steps 8-11** (tests):\n   - Step 8: Handler unit tests for descriptive errors and VariantType\n   - Step 9: Snapshot fallback unit tests\n   - Step 10: Workflow test using Temporal testsuite\n   - Step 11: Run full test suite\n\n## Key Implementation Details\n\n### Snapshot Fallback (steps 6-7)\n- `GetRecentSnapshotLocations(ctx, clusterID, maxAge)` should return snapshot locations ordered newest-first\n- In production_simulator.go, when `LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot` fails with metadata error AND request has no SourcePlanID and no SnapshotAnchorTime (full_cluster path), iterate recent snapshots\n- Use `storageClient.ListObjectNames` similar to `GetSnapshotClosestTo` in service.go\n- The `debug.ErrContextLocationMissing` sentinel error should be used for the metadata check\n\n### Tests (steps 8-11)\n- Read existing test files first to match patterns:\n  - `handler_test.go` uses `fakeSignaler`, `fakeSimulator`, mockery mocks\n  - `handler_component_test.go` uses real DB via pgxtest\n- For workflow test, use `\"go.temporal.io/sdk/testsuite\"` WorkflowTestSuite\n- For snapshot fallback tests, mock the storage client and debug service\n- Match existing code style exactly\n\n### Ferment Step Management\nFor each step, call `start_ferment_step`, do the work, run verify, then `complete_ferment_step` with proper gates. The ferment_id is `019ea6ea-e768-717f-a8f3-63cd6755637b` and phase_id is `phase-1`.\n\nCheck which steps are already started/completed before acting — don't re-start completed steps."},"timestamp":"2026-06-08T11:43:24.695Z","cwd":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast"}
