textForSnapshot(ctx, loc)\n\t\tif fallbackErr == nil {\n\t\t\treturn fallbackContext, nil\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil, err\n}\n```\n\nOK that looks correct. The sentinel error `debug.ErrMetadataMissing` is used.\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Check what the debug service does for `LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot` to see if it returns `ErrMetadataMissing` correctly\n2. Continue with the remaining steps - steps 8-11 which are tests\n\nLet me check the debug service more carefully to make sure the sentinel error is being returned correctly, then proceed to implement and complete the remaining steps.\n\nActually, looking at the debug service code, line 482 and 502 are returning `ErrMetadataMissing`. But I should verify what `LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot` does.\n\nLet me also check the existing test files to understand patterns.\n\nActually, let me first focus on completing the ferment steps. I need to:\n1. Check which steps are already completed\n2. Complete step 6-7 if not completed\n3. Implement steps 8-11\n\nLet me look at existing tests first to understand patterns.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.bash:33","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast && ls services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/*_test.go"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.read:34","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast/services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/handler_test.go","offset":1,"limit":80}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kimchi-dev","model":"kimi-k2.6","usage":{"input":34659,"output":744,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35403,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780919561263,"responseId":"chatcmpl-920a5c93b14378b8"},"timestamp":"2026-06-08T11:53:01.328Z","cwd":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast"