{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"579f64e5-ec19-481","type":"toolResult","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"functions.read:35","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\tmockTx := setupPassthroughTx(t, repo)\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().IncrementCompletedVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, 1).Return(nil)\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().GetAnalysisVariantsByAnalysis(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil, nil).Maybe()\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().CreateChildVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Maybe()\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().IncrementTotalVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Maybe()\n\n\tsignaler := &fakeSignaler{}\n\thandler := NewHandler(repo, mockrebalancerrepo.NewMockDB(t), &fakeSimulator{result: &executortypes.SimulationResult{\n\t\tPlanID:     planID,\n\t\tSavingsPct: &savings,\n\t\tReport: placementcollector.PlacementReport{\n\t\t\tBinUtilizations: []placementcollector.BinUtilization{\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\tTemplateName:        \"template-a\",\n\t\t\t\t\tInstanceType:        \"m5.large\",\n\t\t\t\t\tAllocatableCPU:      4000,\n\t\t\t\t\tRequestedCPU:        500,\n\t\t\t\t\tAllocatableMemBytes: 8 * 1024 * 1024 * 1024,\n\t\t\t\t\tRequestedMemBytes:   1024 * 1024 * 1024,\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t},\n\t}}, signaler, newTestAnalyzer())\n\n\terr := handler.HandleVariant(t.Context(), validHandlerRequest(variantID))\n\tr.NoError(err)\n\tr.Equal(advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantStatusCompleted, completedVariant.Status)\n\tr.NotNil(completedVariant.RebalancingPlanID)\n\tr.Equal(planID, *completedVariant.RebalancingPlanID)\n\tr.NotNil(completedVariant.Result.SavingsPct)\n\tr.Len(signaler.signals, 1)\n\tr.Equal(variantID, signaler.signals[0].AnalysisVariantID)\n\tr.Equal(0, signaler.signals[0].MutationDepth)\n}\n\nfunc TestHandler_BaselineVariantWritesBackToAnalysis(t *testing.T) {\n\tr := require.New(t)\n\tvariantID := uuid.New()\n\tplanID := uuid.New()\n\tsavings := 10.0\n\tvariant := advisorrepo.AnalysisVariant{\n\t\tID:          variantID,\n\t\tAnalysisID:  uuid.New(),\n\t\tVariantType: advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantTypeBaseline,\n\t\tStatus:      advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantStatusPending,\n\t}\n\n\trepo := mockrepo.NewMockRepository(t)\n\trepo.EXPECT().GetAnalysisVariant(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything, variantID).\n\t\tReturn(variant, nil)\n\trepo.EXPECT().IsVariantCanceled(mock.Anything, variantID).Return(false, nil)\n\trepo.EXPECT().IsAnalysisCanceled(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(false, nil)\n\trepo.EXPECT().UpdateAnalysisVariant(mock.Anything, mock.MatchedBy(func(v advisorrepo.AnalysisVariant) bool {\n\t\treturn v.Status == advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantStatusRunning\n\t})).Return(nil).Once()\n\trepo.EXPECT().UpdateAnalysisVariantIfNotTerminal(mock.Anything, mock.MatchedBy(func(v advisorrepo.AnalysisVariant) bool {\n\t\treturn v.Status == advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantStatusCompleted\n\t})).Return(nil).Once()\n\n\tvar capturedBaselineVariantID uuid.UUID\n\tvar capturedBaselineResult advisorrepo.VariantResult\n\tmockTx := setupPassthroughTx(t, repo)\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().IncrementCompletedVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, 1).Return(nil)\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().SetBaselineResult(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything).\n\t\tRunAndReturn(func(_ context.Context, _ uuid.UUID, vid uuid.UUID, res advisorrepo.VariantResult) error {\n\t\t\tcapturedBaselineVariantID = vid\n\t\t\tcapturedBaselineResult = res\n\t\t\treturn nil\n\t\t}).Once()\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().GetAnalysisVariantsByAnalysis(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil, nil).Maybe()\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().CreateChildVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Maybe()\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().IncrementTotalVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Maybe()\n\n\thandler := NewHandler(repo, mockrebalancerrepo.NewMockDB(t), &fakeSimulator{result: &executortypes.SimulationResult{\n\t\tPlanID:     planID,\n\t\tSavingsPct: &savings,\n\t}}, &fakeSignaler{}, newTestAnalyzer())\n\n\tr.NoError(handler.HandleVariant(t.Context(), validHandlerRequest(variantID)))\n\tr.Equal(variantID, capturedBaselineVariantID)\n\tr.NotNil(capturedBaselineResult.SavingsPct)\n\tr.Equal(savings, *capturedBaselineResult.SavingsPct)\n}\n\nfunc TestHandler_MutationVariantDoesNotWriteBaseline(t *testing.T) {\n\tr := require.New(t)\n\tvariantID := uuid.New()\n\tvariant := advisorrepo.AnalysisVariant{\n\t\tID:          variantID,\n\t\tVariantType: advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantTypeMutation,\n\t\tStatus:      advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantStatusPending,\n\t}\n\n\trepo := mockrepo.NewMockRepository(t)\n\trepo.EXPECT().GetAnalysisVariant(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything, variantID).\n\t\tReturn(variant, nil)\n\trepo.EXPECT().IsVariantCanceled(mock.Anything, variantID).Return(false, nil)\n\trepo.EXPECT().IsAnalysisCanceled(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(false, nil)\n\trepo.EXPECT().UpdateAnalysisVariant(mock.Anything, mock.MatchedBy(func(v advisorrepo.AnalysisVariant) bool {\n\t\treturn v.Status == advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantStatusRunning\n\t})).Return(nil).Once()\n\trepo.EXPECT().UpdateAnalysisVariantIfNotTerminal(mock.Anything, mock.MatchedBy(func(v advisorrepo.AnalysisVariant) bool {\n\t\treturn v.Status == advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantStatusCompleted\n\t})).Return(nil).Once()\n\n\tmockTx := setupPassthroughTx(t, repo)\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().IncrementCompletedVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, 1).Return(nil)\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().GetAnalysisVariantsByAnalysis(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil, nil).Maybe()\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().CreateChildVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Maybe()\n\tmockTx.EXPECT().IncrementTotalVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Maybe()\n\n\thandler := NewHandler(repo, mockrebalancerrepo.NewMockDB(t), &fakeSimulator{result: &executortypes.SimulationResult{PlanID: uuid.New()}}, &fakeSignaler{}, newTestAnalyzer())\n\tr.NoError(handler.HandleVariant(t.Context(), validHandlerRequest(variantID)))\n}\n\nfunc TestHandler_SimulationFailureStillSignals(t *testing.T) {\n\tr := require.New(t)\n\tvariantID := uuid.New()\n\tsimErr := errors.New(\"simulation failed\")\n\tvariant := advisorrepo.AnalysisVariant{\n\t\tID:     variantID,\n\t\tStatus: advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantStatusPending,\n\t}\n\n\trepo := mockrepo.NewMockRepository(t)\n\trepo.EXPECT().GetAnalysisVariant(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything, variantID).\n\t\tReturn(variant, nil)\n\trepo.EXPECT().IsVariantCanceled(mock.Anything, variantID).Return(false, nil)\n\trepo.EXPECT().UpdateAnalysisVariant(mock.Anything, mock.MatchedBy(func(v advisorrepo.AnalysisVariant) bool {\n\t\treturn v.Status == advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantStatusRunning\n\t})).Return(nil).Once()\n\n\tvar failedVariant advisorrepo.AnalysisVariant\n\trepo.EXPECT().UpdateAnalysisVariant(mock.Anything, mock.MatchedBy(func(v advisorrepo.AnalysisVariant) bool {\n\t\treturn v.Status == advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantStatusFailed\n\t})).RunAndReturn(func(_ context.Context, v advisorrepo.AnalysisVariant) error {\n\t\tfailedVariant = v\n\t\treturn nil\n\t}).Once()\n\n\tsignaler := &fakeSignaler{}\n\thandler := NewHandler(repo, mockrebalancerrepo.NewMockDB(t), &fakeSimulator{err: simErr}, signaler, newTestAnalyzer())\n\n\terr := handler.HandleVariant(t.Context(), validHandlerRequest(variantID))\n\tr.NoError(err)\n\tr.Equal(advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantStatusFailed, failedVariant.Status)\n\tr.NotNil(failedVariant.Error)\n\tr.Equal(variantFailedUserMessage, *failedVariant.Error)\n\tr.Len(signaler.signals, 1)\n\tr.Equal(variantFailedUserMessage, signaler.signals[0].Error)\n\tr.Equal(0, signaler.signals[0].MutationDepth)\n}\n\nfunc TestHandler_SignalFailureReturnsErrorForRedelivery(t *testing.T) {\n\tr := require.New(t)\n\tsignalErr := errors.New(\"temporal unavailable\")\n\tvariant := advisorrepo.AnalysisVariant{\n\t\tID:     uuid.New(),\n\t\tStatus: advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantStatusCompleted,\n\t}\n\n\trepo := mockrepo.NewMockRepository(t)\n\trepo.EXPECT().GetAnalysisVariant(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything, variant.ID).\n\t\tReturn(variant, nil)\n\n\thandler := NewHandler(repo, mockrebalancerrepo.NewMockDB(t), &fakeSimulator{}, &fakeSignaler{err: signalErr}, newTestAnalyzer())\n\n\terr := handler.HandleVariant(t.Context(), validHandlerRequest(variant.ID))\n\tr.ErrorIs(err, signalErr)\n}\n\nfunc TestHandler_reconstructMutations(t *testing.T) {\n\tr := require.New(t)\n\th := NewHandler(nil, nil, nil, nil, newTestAnalyzer())\n\tgot, err := h.reconstructMutations(t.Context(), advisorrepo.MutationsPayload{Mutations: []advisorrepo.Mutation{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tName:             mutation.NameLowerMinCPU,\n\t\t\tCategory:         detector.CategoryUnderutilizedBins,\n\t\t\tAffectedSubjects: []string{\"template-a\"},\n\t\t\tParams: mutation.MutationParams{MinCPU: &mutation.MinCPUMutationParams{\n\t\t\t\tTemplateName: \"template-a\",\n\t\t\t\tNewMinCPU:    500,\n\t\t\t}},\n\t\t},\n\t}})\n\tr.NoError(err)\n\tr.Len(got, 1)\n\tr.Equal(mutation.NameLowerMinCPU, got[0].Name)\n\tr.NotNil(got[0].Apply)\n}\n\nfunc TestHandler_buildChildMutationSets_DeriveVariantIDIsDeterministic(t *testing.T) {\n\tr := require.New(t)\n\th := NewHandler(nil, nil, nil, nil, newTestAnalyzer())\n\tparentMutations := advisorrepo.MutationsPayload{Mutations: []advisorrepo.Mutation{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tName:             mutation.NameLowerMinCPU,\n\t\t\tCategory:         detector.CategoryUnderutilizedBins,\n\t\t\tAffectedSubjects: []string{\"template-a\"},\n\t\t\tParams: mutation.MutationParams{MinCPU: &mutation.MinCPUMutationParams{\n\n[125 more lines in file. Use offset=281 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780919605210},"timestamp":"2026-06-08T11:53:25.211Z","cwd":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast"}
{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"579f64e5-ec19-481","type":"toolResult","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"functions.read:36","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\t\t\tParams: mutation.MutationParams{MinCPU: &mutation.MinCPUMutationParams{\n\t\t\t\tTemplateName: \"template-a\",\n\t\t\t\tNewMinCPU:    500,\n\t\t\t}},\n\t\t},\n\t}}\n\tgenerated := []mutation.Mutation{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tName:             mutation.NameLowerMinCPU,\n\t\t\tCategory:         detector.CategoryUnderutilizedBins,\n\t\t\tAffectedSubjects: []string{\"template-b\"},\n\t\t\tParams: mutation.MutationParams{MinCPU: &mutation.MinCPUMutationParams{\n\t\t\t\tTemplateName: \"template-b\",\n\t\t\t\tNewMinCPU:    1000,\n\t\t\t}},\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tsets := h.buildChildMutationSets(parentMutations, generated)\n\n\tr.Len(sets, 1)\n\tr.Len(sets[0].Mutations, 2)\n\tanalysisID := uuid.MustParse(\"11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111\")\n\tid1 := advisorrepo.DeriveVariantID(analysisID, sets[0].Mutations)\n\tid2 := advisorrepo.DeriveVariantID(analysisID, []advisorrepo.Mutation{sets[0].Mutations[1], sets[0].Mutations[0]})\n\tr.Equal(id1, id2, \"DeriveVariantID should be order-independent\")\n}\n\nfunc validHandlerRequest(variantID uuid.UUID) mq.AnalysisVariantRequest {\n\treturn mq.AnalysisVariantRequest{\n\t\tAnalysisID:         uuid.New(),\n\t\tAnalysisVariantID:  variantID,\n\t\tClusterID:          uuid.New(),\n\t\tOrganizationID:     uuid.New(),\n\t\tTemporalWorkflowID: \"cluster-advisor-analysis\",\n\t\tMutations: advisorrepo.MutationsPayload{Mutations: []advisorrepo.Mutation{\n\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\tName:             mutation.NameLowerMinCPU,\n\t\t\t\tCategory:         detector.CategoryUnderutilizedBins,\n\t\t\t\tAffectedSubjects: []string{\"template-a\"},\n\t\t\t\tParams: mutation.MutationParams{MinCPU: &mutation.MinCPUMutationParams{\n\t\t\t\t\tTemplateName: \"template-a\",\n\t\t\t\t\tNewMinCPU:    500,\n\t\t\t\t}},\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t}},\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc setupPassthroughTx(t *testing.T, repo *mockrepo.MockRepository) *mockrepo.MockTx {\n\tt.Helper()\n\tmockTx := mockrepo.NewMockTx(t)\n\trepo.EXPECT().WithTx(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything).\n\t\tRunAndReturn(func(ctx context.Context, opts *sql.TxOptions, fn func(advisorrepo.Tx) error) error {\n\t\t\treturn fn(mockTx)\n\t\t})\n\treturn mockTx\n}\n\ntype fakeSimulator struct {\n\tresult *executortypes.SimulationResult\n\terr    error\n}\n\nfunc (s *fakeSimulator) RunVariant(context.Context, mq.AnalysisVariantRequest, []mutation.Mutation) (*executortypes.SimulationResult, string, error) {\n\treturn s.result, \"\", s.err\n}\n\ntype fakeSignaler struct {\n\tsignals []executortypes.AnalysisVariantCompletedSignal\n\terr     error\n}\n\nfunc (s *fakeSignaler) SignalVariantCompleted(_ context.Context, _ string, signal executortypes.AnalysisVariantCompletedSignal) error {\n\ts.signals = append(s.signals, signal)\n\treturn s.err\n}\n\nfunc TestHandler_buildChildMutationSets_FiltersConflictingMutations(t *testing.T) {\n\tr := require.New(t)\n\th := NewHandler(nil, nil, nil, nil, newTestAnalyzer())\n\n\t// Parent already has double-max-pods for \"my-node-config\"\n\tparentMutations := advisorrepo.MutationsPayload{Mutations: []advisorrepo.Mutation{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tName:             mutation.NameDoubleMaxPods,\n\t\t\tCategory:         detector.CategoryPodCountPressure,\n\t\t\tAffectedSubjects: []string{\"my-node-config\"},\n\t\t\tParams: mutation.MutationParams{MaxPods: &mutation.MaxPodsMutationParams{\n\t\t\t\tTemplateName:   \"tmpl\",\n\t\t\t\tNodeConfigName: \"my-node-config\",\n\t\t\t}},\n\t\t},\n\t}}\n\n\t// New analysis generates remove-max-pods-formula for the same node config — must be filtered.\n\tgenerated := []mutation.Mutation{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tName:             mutation.NameRemoveMaxPodsFormula,\n\t\t\tCategory:         detector.CategoryPodCountPressure,\n\t\t\tAffectedSubjects: []string{\"my-node-config\"},\n\t\t\tParams: mutation.MutationParams{MaxPods: &mutation.MaxPodsMutationParams{\n\t\t\t\tTemplateName:   \"tmpl\",\n\t\t\t\tNodeConfigName: \"my-node-config\",\n\t\t\t\tRemoveFormula:  true,\n\t\t\t}},\n\t\t},\n\t\t// Different config — should NOT be filtered.\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tName:             mutation.NameDoubleMaxPods,\n\t\t\tCategory:         detector.CategoryPodCountPressure,\n\t\t\tAffectedSubjects: []string{\"other-config\"},\n\t\t\tParams: mutation.MutationParams{MaxPods: &mutation.MaxPodsMutationParams{\n\t\t\t\tTemplateName:   \"other-tmpl\",\n\t\t\t\tNodeConfigName: \"other-config\",\n\t\t\t}},\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tsets := h.buildChildMutationSets(parentMutations, generated)\n\n\tr.Len(sets, 1, \"conflicting mutation for same node config must be filtered out\")\n\tr.Equal(mutation.NameDoubleMaxPods, sets[0].Mutations[1].Name)\n\tr.Equal([]string{\"other-config\"}, sets[0].Mutations[1].AffectedSubjects)\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780919605210},"timestamp":"2026-06-08T11:53:25.211Z","cwd":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast"}
{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"579f64e5-ec19-481","type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"           Now let me look at the existing test patterns, and also check the production_simulator tests and the workflow tests. Let me also read the handler_component_test.go to understand component tests.\n\nI notice an issue in existing handler_test.go - the `TestHandler_SimulationFailureStillSignals` test checks:\n```go\nr.Equal(variantFailedUserMessage, *failedVariant.Error)\nr.Equal(variantFailedUserMessage, signaler.signals[0].Error)\n```\n\nBut now with the new code, `failVariant` uses:\n```go\nmsg := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", variantFailedUserMessage, sanitizeErrorMessage(cause))\n```\n\nSo the error message now includes the cause. But the existing test still checks for `variantFailedUserMessage` which is just `\"simulation failed\"`. The test is expecting `\"simulation failed\"` but the new code produces `\"simulation failed: simulation failed\"`. \n\nWait, let me re-read the sanitizeErrorMessage function:\n```go\nfunc sanitizeErrorMessage(cause error) string {\n\tmsg := cause.Error()\n\treturn msg\n}\n```\n\nIt's just returning the error string as-is. And then:\n```go\nmsg := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", variantFailedUserMessage, sanitizeErrorMessage(cause))\n```\n\nSo for `simErr := errors.New(\"simulation failed\")`, the final message would be `\"simulation failed: simulation failed\"`.\n\nBut the existing test expects `\"simulation failed\"` for both the variant error and the signal error. This test needs to be updated, or we need to adjust the code.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the spec: \"the variant error message exposed to users includes the root cause (e.g. 'simulation failed: snapshot does not contain required location metadata') instead of the generic 'simulation failed'\".\n\nSo the existing test `TestHandler_SimulationFailureStillSignals` needs to be updated to expect the new format. Let me run the existing tests first to see what fails.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.bash:37","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast/services/autoscaler && go test ./internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/ -run TestHandler_SimulationFailureStillSignals -v 2>&1","timeout":60}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kimchi-dev","model":"kimi-k2.6","usage":{"input":39826,"output":476,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40302,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780919605213,"responseId":"chatcmpl-a3f6d7ab5abbc435"},"timestamp":"2026-06-08T11:54:07.994Z","cwd":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast"}
