{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"579f64e5-ec19-481","type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"            As expected, the existing test fails because the error message format changed. I need to update the test and check for other failures too. Let me first run the full existing test suite to see all failures, then fix them.\n\nActually, looking at the test, it seems like the test passes `simErr := errors.New(\"simulation failed\")` but the handler now prefixes it with `\"simulation failed: \"` so the result is `\"simulation failed: simulation failed\"`. \n\nLooking at the normal failure path when the simulator returns an error: the actual error would be something like `\"snapshot metadata missing\"`, and the final message would be `\"simulation failed: snapshot metadata missing\"`. In the test, the mock error is `\"simulation failed\"` which makes the result `\"simulation failed: simulation failed\"` - a bit redundant in the test but correct in production.\n\nI should update the test to expect the new format. Let me fix it first, then run all existing tests.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.bash:38","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast/services/autoscaler && go test ./internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/ -v 2>&1 | tail -40","timeout":120}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kimchi-dev","model":"kimi-k2.6","usage":{"input":40623,"output":265,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40888,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780919647996,"responseId":"chatcmpl-96853ccbbf308005"},"timestamp":"2026-06-08T11:55:13.771Z","cwd":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast"}
