{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"579f64e5-ec19-481","type":"toolResult","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"functions.read:55","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"func (s *service) LoadRebalancerDependenciesForSnapshot(ctx context.Context, snapshotLocation string) (*model_types.ModelDependencies, error) {\n\tcc, err := s.LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot(ctx, snapshotLocation)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\treturn cc.ModelDependencies, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *service) LoadRebalancerClusterContextForSnapshot(ctx context.Context, snapshotLocation string) (*ClusterContext, error) {\n\tsnapshotPath, err := s.snapshotClient.ObjectNameFromFullPath(ctx, snapshotLocation)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parsing snapshot path: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tcontextLocation, err := GetRebalancerDebugContextLocationForSnapshot(ctx, s.snapshotClient, snapshotPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\treturn s.loadClusterContextFromLocation(ctx, contextLocation)\n}\n\nfunc (s *service) loadDependenciesFromContextLocation(ctx context.Context, contextLocation string) (*model_types.ModelDependencies, error) {\n\tcc, err := s.loadClusterContextFromLocation(ctx, contextLocation)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\treturn cc.ModelDependencies, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *service) loadClusterContextFromLocation(ctx context.Context, contextLocation string) (*ClusterContext, error) {\n\tdebugContextPath, err := s.debugClient.ObjectNameFromFullPath(ctx, contextLocation)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parsing debug context path: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tdebugContext, err := LoadDebugContext(ctx, s.debugClient, debugContextPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\treturn getClusterContextFromDebugContext(ctx, s.debugClient, debugContext)\n}\n\nfunc GetDebugContextLocationForSnapshot(ctx context.Context, snapshotStorage storage.Storage, snapshotPath string) (string, error) {\n\tsnapshotAttrs, err := resolveSnapshotAttrs(ctx, snapshotStorage, snapshotPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", err\n\t}\n\n\tcontextLocation, exists := snapshotAttrs[MetadataDebugContextLocation]\n\tif !exists {\n\t\treturn \"\", ErrMetadataMissing\n\t}\n\n\treturn contextLocation, nil\n}\n\n// GetRebalancerDebugContextLocationForSnapshot returns the debug context location for a snapshot,\n// preferring MetadataRebalancerDebugContextLocation and falling back to MetadataDebugContextLocation.\nfunc GetRebalancerDebugContextLocationForSnapshot(ctx context.Context, snapshotStorage storage.Storage, snapshotPath string) (string, error) {\n\tsnapshotAttrs, err := resolveSnapshotAttrs(ctx, snapshotStorage, snapshotPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", err\n\t}\n\n\tif loc, ok := snapshotAttrs[MetadataRebalancerDebugContextLocation]; ok {\n\t\treturn loc, nil\n\t}\n\tif loc, ok := snapshotAttrs[MetadataDebugContextLocation]; ok {\n\t\treturn loc, nil\n\t}\n\treturn \"\", ErrMetadataMissing\n}\n\n// resolveSnapshotAttrs fetches metadata for snapshotPath, following the btrsp origin header if present.\nfunc resolveSnapshotAttrs(ctx context.Context, snapshotStorage storage.Storage, snapshotPath string) (map[string]string, error) {\n\tattrs, err := snapshotStorage.GetMetadata(ctx, snapshotPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\tif origin, ok := attrs[snapshots_v2.OriginHeader]; ok {\n\t\toriginPath, err := snapshots_v2.ParseBtrspOrigin(origin)\n\t\tif err == nil {\n\t\t\tsnapshotPath, err = snapshotStorage.ObjectNameFromFullPath(ctx, originPath)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parsing object name: %w\", err)\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tattrs, err = snapshotStorage.GetMetadata(ctx, snapshotPath)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn nil, err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn attrs, nil\n}\n\n\n[388 more lines in file. Use offset=530 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780919971785},"timestamp":"2026-06-08T11:59:31.787Z","cwd":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast"}
{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"579f64e5-ec19-481","type":"toolResult","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"functions.read:56","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"package snapshots\n\nimport (\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\t\"github.com/google/uuid\"\n\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/mock\"\n\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n\tv1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\n\t\"github.com/castai/kubecast/lib/btrsp\"\n\tsnapshots_v2_mocks \"github.com/castai/kubecast/lib/snapshots-client/mocks/v2\"\n\tsnapshots_v2 \"github.com/castai/kubecast/lib/snapshots-client/v2\"\n)\n\nfunc TestGetLatestSnapshot(t *testing.T) {\n\ttests := map[string]struct {\n\t\tconfigureMocksFn func(t *testing.T, v2Client *snapshots_v2_mocks.MockClient)\n\t\texpectedErr      error\n\t}{\n\t\t\"loads latest snapshot from v2 client\": {\n\t\t\tconfigureMocksFn: func(t *testing.T, v2Client *snapshots_v2_mocks.MockClient) {\n\t\t\t\tv2Client.EXPECT().GetLatestSnapshot(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(&snapshots_v2.Snapshot{}, nil).Times(1)\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t},\n\t\t\"returns error on failure\": {\n\t\t\tconfigureMocksFn: func(t *testing.T, v2Client *snapshots_v2_mocks.MockClient) {\n\t\t\t\tv2Client.EXPECT().GetLatestSnapshot(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil, errors.New(\"failed\")).Times(1)\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\texpectedErr: errors.New(\"failed\"),\n\t\t},\n\t\t\"returns not found if on not found error\": {\n\t\t\tconfigureMocksFn: func(t *testing.T, v2Client *snapshots_v2_mocks.MockClient) {\n\t\t\t\tv2Client.EXPECT().GetLatestSnapshot(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil, snapshots_v2.ErrNotFound).Times(1)\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\texpectedErr: ErrSnapshotNotFound,\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tfor name, tt := range tests {\n\t\tt.Run(name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\tt.Parallel()\n\t\t\tr := require.New(t)\n\n\t\t\tv2Client := snapshots_v2_mocks.NewMockClient(t)\n\t\t\tclusterID := uuid.New()\n\n\t\t\tif tt.configureMocksFn != nil {\n\t\t\t\ttt.configureMocksFn(t, v2Client)\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tservice := NewService(v2Client, v2Client, nil)\n\n\t\t\tsnap, err := service.GetLatestSnapshot(t.Context(), clusterID)\n\t\t\tif tt.expectedErr != nil {\n\t\t\t\tr.Error(err)\n\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tr.NoError(err)\n\t\t\tr.NotNil(snap)\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestGetSnapshot(t *testing.T) {\n\tv1SnapshotName := \"gs://snapshotstore/cluster/2025-10-15T10:01:05.153917058Z-snapshot.json.gz\"\n\tv2SnapshotName := \"gs://snapshotstore/cluster/2025-10-15T10:01:05.153917058Z.diff.btrsp\"\n\t// The service strips the full path down to just the filename before calling the client.\n\tv2SnapshotFilename := \"2025-10-15T10:01:05.153917058Z.diff.btrsp\"\n\n\ttests := map[string]struct {\n\t\tsnapshotName     string\n\t\tconfigureMocksFn func(t *testing.T, v2Client *snapshots_v2_mocks.MockClient)\n\t\texpectedErr      error\n\t}{\n\t\t\"loads v2 snapshot from v2 client\": {\n\t\t\tconfigureMocksFn: func(t *testing.T, v2Client *snapshots_v2_mocks.MockClient) {\n\t\t\t\tv2Client.EXPECT().GetSnapshot(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, v2SnapshotFilename).Return(&snapshots_v2.Snapshot{}, nil).Times(1)\n\n[159 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780919971785},"timestamp":"2026-06-08T11:59:31.787Z","cwd":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast"}
{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"579f64e5-ec19-481","type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"                  Now I have a good understanding of the test patterns. Let me now plan what tests to add:\n\n1. **Handler test for descriptive error message** - I already updated the existing `TestHandler_SimulationFailureStillSignals`\n2. **Handler test for VariantType in signal** - need to add a test that verifies VariantType is set\n3. **Snapshot fallback tests** - need to test `production_simulator.loadContextWithFallback`\n4. **Workflow test** - need Temporal testsuite test\n\nLet me look at what pattern is used for the existing `fakeSimulator` and then create a new test file or add to handler_test.go.\n\nActually, let me first check if there are any existing tests that cover snapshot fallback, then add tests for the new behavior.\n\nLet me also check the mock for simulation runtime to understand how to test production_simulator.go.\n\nNow, let me first fix the existing test that I already broke, then add new tests. The existing test fix is already done. Let me now add the new tests.\n\nFor the handler tests, I need to add:\n1. Test for variant type in signal (for baseline and mutation)\n2. Test for descriptive error message\n\nActually, the existing tests already implicitly test some of this. Let me add focused tests.\n\nFor the snapshot fallback tests, I need to test `production_simulator.loadContextWithFallback`. The function is a method on `productionSimulator`, so I'll need to construct a `productionSimulator` with mocked dependencies.\n\nFor the workflow test using Temporal testsuite, I need to understand what's available.\n\nLet me first check what temporal testsuite imports look like.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.bash:57","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast && grep -r \"go.temporal.io/sdk/tests