{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"579f64e5-ec19-481","type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"             The `mockTx` doesn't have `IsAnalysisCanceled`. It's on the repo, not the tx. Let me check the handler.go code. Looking at the handler:\n\n```go\nif err := h.repo.WithTx(ctx, nil, func(tx advisorrepo.Tx) error {\n    ...\n    analysisCanceled, _ := h.repo.IsAnalysisCanceled(ctx, req.AnalysisID)\n```\n\nOh, the `IsAnalysisCanceled` is called on `h.repo`, not `tx`. Let me check what mock is needed. Actually, looking at the handler code:\n\n```go\nif err := h.repo.WithTx(ctx, nil, func(tx advisorrepo.Tx) error {\n    if err := tx.IncrementCompletedVariants(ctx, req.AnalysisID, 1); err != nil {\n        logging.FromContext(ctx).WithError(err).Errorf(\"incrementing completed variants for analysis %s\", req.AnalysisID)\n    }\n    if variant.VariantType == advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantTypeBaseline {\n        if err := tx.SetBaselineResult(ctx, req.AnalysisID, variant.ID, variant.Result); err != nil {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"setting baseline result: %w\", err)\n        }\n    }\n    // Do not spawn children if the analysis was canceled while this variant was running.\n    analysisCanceled, _ := h.repo.IsAnalysisCanceled(ctx, req.AnalysisID)\n```\n\nThe `IsAnalysisCanceled` is called on `h.repo` inside the `WithTx` callback. But looking at the existing `TestHandler_BaselineVariantWritesBackToAnalysis` test, it sets up:\n\n```go\nmockTx := setupPassthroughTx(t, repo)\nmockTx.EXPECT().IncrementCompletedVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, 1).Return(nil)\nmockTx.EXPECT().SetBaselineResult(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Once()\nmockTx.EXPECT().GetAnalysisVariantsByAnalysis(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil, nil).Maybe()\n```\n\nAnd `IsAnalysisCanceled` is called on repo already. Let me check the WithTx pattern in the existing tests. Looking at `setupPassthroughTx`:\n\n```go\nfunc setupPassthroughTx(t *testing.T, repo *mockrepo.MockRepository) *mockrepo.MockTx {\n    t.Helper()\n    mockTx := mockrepo.NewMockTx(t)\n    repo.EXPECT().WithTx(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything).\n        RunAndReturn(func(ctx context.Context, opts *sql.TxOptions, fn func(advisorrepo.Tx) error) error {\n            return fn(mockTx)\n        })\n    return mockTx\n}\n```\n\nSo `IsAnalysisCanceled` inside the WithTx will be called after WithTx returns... Actually wait, let me re-read. The `IsAnalysisCanceled` is called BEFORE `WithTx` in `TestHandler_SuccessfulVariant`:\n\n```go\nrepo.EXPECT().IsAnalysisCanceled(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(false, nil)\n```\n\nThis is on the repo! And the `WithTx` just passes control to callback. Inside the callback, `IsAnalysisCanceled` is on the repo. But wait, I see in `TestHandler_SuccessfulVariant` that `IsAnalysisCanceled` is set on the repo directly. Let me re-check the handler code.\n\nLooking at handler.go:\n```go\nif err := h.repo.WithTx(ctx, nil, func(tx advisorrepo.Tx) error {\n    if err := tx.IncrementCompletedVariants(ctx, req.AnalysisID, 1); err != nil {\n        logging.FromContext(ctx).WithError(err).Errorf(\"incrementing completed variants for analysis %s\", req.AnalysisID)\n    }\n    if variant.VariantType == advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantTypeBaseline {\n        if err := tx.SetBaselineResult(ctx, req.AnalysisID, variant.ID, variant.Result); err != nil {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"setting baseline result: %w\", err)\n        }\n    }\n    // Do not spawn children if the analysis was canceled while this variant was running.\n    analysisCanceled, _ := h.repo.IsAnalysisCanceled(ctx, req.AnalysisID)\n    if !analysisCanceled {\n        if maxDepth := req.MaxDepth; maxDepth == 0 || variant.MutationDepth < maxDepth {\n            if err := h.createChildVariants(ctx, tx, variant, childMutationSets); err != nil {\n                logging.FromContext(ctx).WithError(err).Errorf(\"creating child variants for %s\", variant.ID)\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    return nil\n}); err != nil {\n```\n\nWait, `h.repo.IsAnalysisCanceled` is used inside the WithTx callback. But since `h.repo` is the same repo object, the mock still applies. Let me remove the wrong mock from my test.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.edit:75","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast/services/autoscaler/internal/services/clusteradvisor/executor/handler_test.go","edits":[{"oldText":"\t\t\tmockTx := setupPassthroughTx(t, repo)\n\t\t\tmockTx.EXPECT().IncrementCompletedVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, 1).Return(nil)\n\t\t\tif tt.variantType == advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantTypeBaseline {\n\t\t\t\tmockTx.EXPECT().SetBaselineResult(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Once()\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tmockTx.EXPECT().IsAnalysisCanceled(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(false, nil)\n\t\t\tmockTx.EXPECT().GetAnalysisVariantsByAnalysis(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil, nil).Maybe()\n\t\t\tmockTx.EXPECT().CreateChildVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Maybe()\n\t\t\tmockTx.EXPECT().IncrementTotalVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Maybe()","newText":"\t\t\tmockTx := setupPassthroughTx(t, repo)\n\t\t\tmockTx.EXPECT().IncrementCompletedVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, 1).Return(nil)\n\t\t\tif tt.variantType == advisorrepo.AnalysisVariantTypeBaseline {\n\t\t\t\tmockTx.EXPECT().SetBaselineResult(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Once()\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tmockTx.EXPECT().GetAnalysisVariantsByAnalysis(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil, nil).Maybe()\n\t\t\tmockTx.EXPECT().CreateChildVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Maybe()\n\t\t\tmockTx.EXPECT().IncrementTotalVariants(mock.Anything, mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil).Maybe()"}]}}],"api