{"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"579f64e5-ec19-481","type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"        The issue is that `loadSourcePlan` returns `snapshotLocation = \"\"` because `GetLatestSnapshot` returns a testing snapshot but `SnapshotLocation()` returns `\"\"` for a testing snapshot that doesn't have a location set. Looking at `loadSourcePlan`:\n\n```go\nif req.SourcePlanID == nil {\n    snap, err := s.snapshotService.GetLatestSnapshot(ctx, req.ClusterID)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"getting latest snapshot for cluster %s: %w\", req.ClusterID, err)\n    }\n    return &rebalancingrepo.Plan{SnapshotLocation: snap.SnapshotLocation()}, nil\n}\n```\n\nAnd `MutableSnapshot.SnapshotLocation()`:\n```go\nfunc (m *Snapshot) SnapshotLocation() string {\n    if strings.Contains(m.Snapshot.SnapshotLocation(), \"btrsp\") {\n        return m.Snapshot.SnapshotDiffLocation()\n    }\n    return m.Snapshot.SnapshotLocation()\n}\n```\n\nThe testing snapshot doesn't have a location set, so it returns \"\". I need to set the location on the testing snapshot.\n\nLet me check if `TestingSnapshot` has a way to set the location.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.bash:104","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast && grep -n \"NewTestingSnapshot\\|TestingSnapshot\" lib/snapshots-client/v2/types.go | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.bash:105","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/laimonasrastenis/Projects/kubecast && grep -rn \"NewTestingSnapshot\" lib/snapshots-client/ | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kimchi-dev","model":"kimi-k2.6","usage":{"input":95603,"output":345,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95948,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780921998116,"responseId":"chatcmpl-92b428e